{"questionId":"2c578582-a4c6-4b17-a43d-0f06aaab91b7_8","correctAnswer":"D","section":"Math","steps":[{"title":"Solve the system by substitution","content":"Substitute $y=3x+9$ into $3y=8x-6$: $$3(3x+9)=8x-6 \\Rightarrow 9x+27=8x-6 \\Rightarrow x=-33.$$ Then $y=3(-33)+9=-90$."},{"title":"Find $x - y$","content":"So $x-y=-33-(-90)=57$. That matches choice <strong>D</strong> — <strong>D</strong> is correct."}]}